&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor and day-to-day partner to the CEO and CFO, managing priorities, decision-making cadence, and information flow across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, synthesize, and escalate strategic issues before they become problems — keeping both principals appropriately focused on what matters most.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-functional initiatives on behalf of the CEO and CFO, holding teams accountable and removing blockers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare briefing materials, decision memos, and strategic analyses to support executive decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the operating rhythm of the executive office, including leadership team meetings, quarterly business reviews, and offsites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate customer insights from the CEO&#39;s sales conversations into structured product asks, partnering with product and engineering leads to prioritize them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a single source of truth on top-priority initiatives so leadership has visibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project manage CRM hygiene, pipeline reporting cadences, and weekly sales reviews so the team has clean data and clear next steps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
